{
  "number": 3094,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3094",
  "title": "Discrepancy between sortBy and transformItems",
  "body": "**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\nIn refinenementList, `sortBy` and `transformItems` do not work on the same type of items.\r\n\r\nIn sortBy the objects are the ones manipulated in the helper with the following keys:\r\n - name\r\n - count\r\n - isRefined\r\n\r\nIn transformItems, items have the following keys:\r\n - label (equivalent of name)\r\n - value (legacy, comes from the SFFV API)\r\n - count\r\n - isRefined\r\n - highlighted (for SFFV)\r\n\r\nAs a user you have to figure out the shape of the object and it's tricky to handle two versions of similar things that are not unified. Also sortBy doesn't work on sffv. Finally the sortBy is implemented at the Helper level which makes it hard to unify it with the transformItems API.\r\n\r\n**Expected API 💭**\r\n\r\nOnly have one way to sort (transformItems) or implement sortBy at the IS.js level so that we can use the same standardized structure for the facet items.",
